          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Minimum",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " function is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server designed to return the smallest value from a set of input values. Scalar functions operate on a single value and return a single value. This function is typically used to determine the minimum value among a set of numeric inputs, which can be useful in various business scenarios such as finding the lowest price, minimum score, or smallest measurement."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Low"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The complexity level of the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Minimum",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " scalar function is considered low. Scalar functions generally involve straightforward logic and operate on a single row at a time, making them relatively simple to implement and understand. The logic for determining the minimum value among a set of inputs is typically uncomplicated."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
