          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " function takes multiple input parameters, each representing a numeric value. These parameters are used to determine the smallest value among them. The function can be designed to accept a variable number of parameters, allowing flexibility in its usage. Each parameter is expected to be of a numeric data type, such as "
        },
