      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "6. Performance Considerations"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Scalar functions can have performance implications when used in SQL queries, especially if they are called repeatedly for each row in a large dataset. This is because scalar functions are executed row-by-row, which can lead to performance bottlenecks. To mitigate this, it is advisable to limit the use of scalar functions in SELECT statements or consider alternative approaches, such as using inline table-valued functions or incorporating the logic directly into the query."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "7. Potential Issues or Risks"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
